<li><strong>Input the external diameter</strong> of the cylinder in the "Di=
ameter external" box. Let's say it equals 10 cm.</li>
<li><strong>Input the internal diameter</strong> of the cylinder in the "Di=
ameter internal" box. Let's say it equals 5 cm.</li>
<li>The cylinder volume should be <strong>1178.1 cm<sup>3</sup></strong>. T=
hat's how you calculate the volume of a hollow cylinder with this tool.</li=
>
</ol>
